#. type: Title =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "About GBIF "
msgstr "Acerca de GBIF "

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:6
msgid "The Global Biodiversity Information Facility (GBIF) is an international network of country and organizational Participants that exists to enable free and open access to biodiversity data from all sources and to support biodiversity science, environmental research, and evidence based decision-making."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:8
msgid "GBIF operates as a federated system of distributed data publishing efforts, coordinated through a global informatics infrastructure and collaborative network."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:10
msgid "In this module, you will learn more about GBIF."
msgstr ""

#.  Note the lack of empty lines between the end of the question (....) and the start of the next question
#.  (. What…) is required, so I have added // comments to help separate them.
#.  The + connects the question into the numbered list item, see https://docs.asciidoctor.org/asciidoc/latest/lists/continuation/
#.  Question 1
#. type: delimited block *
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:12
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:499
#, no-wrap
msgid "What is GBIF?"
msgstr "¿Qué es GBIF?"

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:17
msgid "Can you imagine how much knowledge could be generated, if people could find and use the Earth's biodiversity data, in an organized and accessible way?"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:19
msgid "This video (03:19) was originally co-produced in https://vimeo.com/236573907[Spanish^] by SiB Colombia and GBIF Spain, both national nodes of GBIF, and Go Visual with co-financing from GBIF Spain and the Alexander von Humboldt Biological Resources Research Institute (IAvH), the host institution of SiB Colombia."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:21
