#. type: Title =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:28
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/index.adoc:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "Introduction to GBIF"
msgstr "Introducción a GBIF"

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:33
msgid "In this video (07:40), Kyle Copas, GBIF Head of Communications, provides a brief introduction to GBIF—who we are, what we do, and why we do it."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:35
msgid "If you are unable to watch the embedded Vimeo video, you can xref:attachment$introduction_to_gbif_v1_1080p.mp4[download] it locally (MP4 - 35.8 MB)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:52
#, no-wrap
msgid "intro-to-gbif::intro-to-gbif_Slide1.png"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:55
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Slide 1 - Introduction to GBIF*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:57
msgid "Hi! My name is Kyle Copas, and I’m head of communications at GBIF, the Global Biodiversity Information Facility. I’m pleased to offer this brief introduction to GBIF—who we are, what we do, and why we do it—in hope of providing some context for your training course and encourage you to apply the skills you will acquire to promote GBIF's vision for “A world in which the best possible biodiversity data underpins research, policy and decisions.”"
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:58
#, no-wrap
msgid "intro-to-gbif::intro-to-gbif_Slide2.png"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:61
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Slide 2 - What is GBIF?*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:63
msgid "So what is GBIF? We are an international network and data infrastructure, whose purpose is to provide anyone, anywhere, free and open access to data about all types of life on earth.  This data provides an essential source of evidence for open science that is used across science and policy, supported and advanced by a worldwide community of experts, partners and collaborators."
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:64
#, no-wrap
msgid "intro-to-gbif::intro-to-gbif_Slide3.png"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:67
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Slide 3 - GBIF governance and structure*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:69
msgid "Established in 2001, GBIF operates on the basis of a voluntary Memorandum of Understanding between the governments and transnational organizations that collaborate as GBIF’s formal Participants. The MOU sets out the basic governance and principles for a coordinated international scientific effort to mobilize the data, skills and technologies needed to make comprehensive biodiversity information freely available for science and decision-making. Under the MoU, Participants agree to establish a formal delegation that represents them in GBIF’s governance and also to set up a node, which serves as the focal point for coordinating data sharing and use in their country or organization. The GBIF Secretariat based in Copenhagen, Denmark, manages the technical infrastructure and supports collaborations that keep GBIF going and growing as a global community."
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:70
#, no-wrap
msgid "intro-to-gbif::intro-to-gbif_Slide4.png"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:73
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Slide 4 - Why do countries join GBIF?*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:75
msgid "Governments around the world join GBIF to build on and benefit from the community-based tools, standards, and practices developed and supported the network. This provides an efficient and effective means for Participants to build capacity and address data needs around biodiversity. GBIF helps its participants increase the returns on investment in research, data collection and digitization, create and coordinate partnerships aligned with national efforts, and guide efforts to provide data needed to fulfil national policy goals and global commitments."
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:76
#, no-wrap
msgid "intro-to-gbif::intro-to-gbif_Slide5.png"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:79
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Slide 5 - Governance and structure overview*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:81
msgid "The GBIF governing board meets annually to approve a work programme and make decisions that guide the direction of the network. Board members consist of Participant heads of delegation who represent their countries and organizations. Only Voting Participant Countries that make financial contributions to GBIF's annual budget have the right to vote. Associate Country Participants do not yet make financial contributions and can maintain this temporary status for up to five years, while Associate Organizational Participants are not required to make financial contributions. While Associate Participants cannot vote, delegations from all Participants take part in Governing Board discussions, endorse data publishers, and collaborate in meetings, programmes and other network activities. In between governing board meetings, and under the direction of an elected board chair, the elected members of standing committees for budget, science, nodes and the executive provide oversight and decision-making on operational activities led by the respective teams in the Secretariat."
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:82
#, no-wrap
msgid "intro-to-gbif::intro-to-gbif_Slide6.png"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:85
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Slide 6 - What is a GBIF Participant node?*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:87
msgid "Participant nodes act as focal points for coordinating networks of people and institutions that share and use biodiversity data in their countries and organizations. Supported by their organizational arrangements and GBIF’s common set of informatics solutions, nodes work to improve the availability and quality of biodiversity data. Effective nodes serve as knowledge hubs for both biodiversity data and wider related activities, guiding their audiences toward relevant sources of data and sharing expertise on open data and open science, data standards and digitization, and other biodiversity tools and initiatives."
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:88
#, no-wrap
msgid "intro-to-gbif::intro-to-gbif_Slide7.png"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:91
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Slide 7 - Providing biodiversity evidence for research and policy*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:93
msgid "This diagramme charts the flows and processes by which GBIF brings together data from disparate sources and thousands of institutions using shared tools, common data standards and open licences. The underlying evidence can take many different forms—from museum specimens and field observations from surveys and monitoring programmes, including citizen science projects, to sensor-based sources like camera traps, acoustic recorders, and barcodes sampled from environmental DNA. Taken together, these combined sources provide a more complete view of where and when species have been observed. Users access the resulting index through various methods and formats, which they then apply across a full spectrum of biodiversity-related research and policy."
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:94
#, no-wrap
msgid "intro-to-gbif::intro-to-gbif_Slide8.png"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:97
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Slide 8 - GBIF is used across all domains and disciplines of science*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:99
msgid "Today, GBIF is a mature network and infrastructure used across all domains and disciplines of science. The data that the network integrates not only facilitates global research and access, but also enables researchers to explore both basic and applied questions at taxonomic, temporal and spatial scales that would be otherwise impossible."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block _
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:102
msgid "Heberling JM et al. (2021) Data integration enables global biodiversity synthesis. PNAS 118(6): e2018093118. https://doi.org/10.1073/pnas.2018093118."
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:104
#, no-wrap
msgid "intro-to-gbif::intro-to-gbif_Slide9.png"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:107
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Slide 9 - Big data for biodiversity enables scientific research*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:110
msgid "The Secretariat maintains a sophisticated https://www.gbif.org/literature-tracking[citation tracking system^] to record dozens of journal articles published every week that rely on GBIF-mediated data. Doing so allows GBIF to credit data publishers and to highlight important and illustrative applications of the data in its annual https://www.gbif.org/science-review [Science Review^]. The examples contained in each issue—which also appear online throughout the year—provide a convenient way to understand how data is used in both basic and applied research."
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:111
#, no-wrap
msgid "intro-to-gbif::intro-to-gbif_Slide10.png"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:114
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Slide 10 - Data supports GBF indicators & targets*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:116
msgid "GBIF-mediated data is also an essential input for biodiversity-related policy. Thousands of IUCN Red List assessments, which analyse extinction risks to species, cite occurrence data from GBIF. The same data serves both directly and indirectly as a foundation for metrics and indicators that chart progress toward international targets commitments such as the https://www.cbd.int/gbf[Kunming-Montreal Global Biodiversity Framework^]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:117
#, no-wrap
msgid "intro-to-gbif::intro-to-gbif_Slide11.png"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:120
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Slide 11 - Capacity building for biodiversity data mobilization and use*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:122
msgid "While GBIF delivers many technical solutions, its global community is equally essential, with each individual committed to collaborating and developing skills and best practices for managing, sharing and using biodiversity data. GBIF communities of practice generate, adapt, share and improve freely available tools, guidance documentation, and other learning resources, and then extend their reach further by contributing volunteer translations in multiple languages. Experienced practitioners from GBIF’s nodes and publishers serve as mentors and trainers in courses like the one you're following now, which lie at the heart of GBIF’s work. Today’s trainees soon become tomorrow’s mentors, growing the network through a host of programmes, partnerships and collaborations at many scales."
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:123
#, no-wrap
msgid "intro-to-gbif::intro-to-gbif_Slide12.png"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:128
msgid "So thanks, best of luck and welcome to the GBIF community—and good luck!"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:130
msgid "This video is part of a series of presentations developed for the Introduction to GBIF course. It was created and narrated by me, Kyle Copas. If you have any questions on the course content, you can reach out at training@gbif.org."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:134
#, no-wrap
msgid "GBIF for Science"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:139
msgid "In this video (07:52), Dmitry Schigel, GBIF Lead Scientific Officer, illustrates GBIF’s work in building the evidence to advance scientific research and understanding of global biodiversity."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:141
msgid "If you are unable to watch the embedded Vimeo video, you can xref:attachment$gbif_for_science_v1-1080p.mp4[download] it locally (MP4 - 39.4 MB)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:158
#, no-wrap
msgid "intro-to-gbif::GBIF-for-Science-Slide1.png"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:161
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Slide 1 - GBIF for Science*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:163
msgid "This presentation illustrates GBIF’s work in building the evidence to advance scientific research and understanding of global biodiversity."
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:164
#, no-wrap
msgid "intro-to-gbif::GBIF-for-Science-Slide2.png"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:167
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Slide 2 - Providing biodiversity evidence for research and policy*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:169
msgid "Let’s take a look at GBIF from the science point of view. Let’s work though this left to right."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:171
msgid "On the left, academic organizations such as museums and universities, as well as, governmental agencies and non-governmental organizations, businesses and amateur communities, all can register as data holders in GBIF and share biodiversity data that are borne under their roofs and affiliations."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:173
msgid "Primary biodiversity evidence can have physical objects behind it, like samples and specimens, or it could also be virtual recordings by humans or by automated sensors."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:175
msgid "Some samples undergo chemical processing to reveal biodiversity signals, for instance, through DNA from soil, water, air, or wood. The same method is widely applied to individual or bulk specimens, and together these form eDNA, barcoding, and metabarcoding body of evidence."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:177
msgid "This variety of sources and methods comes together in the central index at GBIF – this index makes searches, filters and machine queries work across all the datasets shared with GBIF."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:179
msgid "On the right side, you see the meaning of GBIF’s existence: GBIF provides efficiency and time saving for data discovery and data access – but we do not resolve data heterogeneity for you. Like with any other internet search, your science needs – on the right in magenta – or, perhaps, your policy needs, in blue, dictate which data records will be fit for your use."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:181
msgid "So here biodiversity science happens on on both sides – on the left, among the data publishers, and on the right – with the users. Biodiversity informatics, computer science with their technical competencies bring the two sides together."
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:182
#, no-wrap
msgid "intro-to-gbif::GBIF-for-Science-Slide3.png"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:185
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Slide 3 - Datasets: attribution, credit and affiliation*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:187
msgid "For anyone in research and academia, the dataset page at GBIF will have familiar elements which focus on credit and attribution:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:189
msgid "First, is the dataset’s organizational affiliation – which is also a link leading to publisher’s page – in GBIF, datasets are shared by organizations."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:191
msgid "Next – are the dataset’s authors in a few key roles – the dataset originators, the creative authors of the recorded biodiversity evidence, and the metadata authors – whose role is to ensure that digital representation and description of the dataset at GBIF is accurate."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:193
msgid "Third – every dataset page where at least one record was cited at least once displays an ever-growing number and links to research papers which are powered by this dataset’s use."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:195
msgid "The fourth and final element highlighted here – is the dataset’s DOI, the unique digital object identifier which enables what we call literature tracking. Anytime data is used from a dataset, the DOI of the dataset is meant to be cited by the users of the data."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:197
msgid "In this particular example, a https://doi.org/10.15468/ajkhha[dataset on bryophytes^], mosses from Switzerland, has been used in a https://doi.org/10.15468/dl.36wam3[study analyzing climate and distribution of Sphagnum mosses^] by a group of authors based in Sweden. This is only one of over 150 studies that are rooted in this dataset."
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:198
#, no-wrap
msgid "intro-to-gbif::GBIF-for-Science-Slide4.png"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:201
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Slide 4 - Peer-reviewed publications using GBIF-mediated data*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:203
msgid "Through the Secretariat’s https://www.gbif.org/literature-tracking[literature tracking programme^], we are able to see that GBIF-mediated data are used in scientific literature at an increasing rate."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:205
msgid "The https://www.gbif.org/science-review[GBIF Science Review^] highlights an annual selection of key research uses drawn from the literature tracking programme. The peer-reviewed articles summarized in the Review offer a partial but instructive view of the wide range of research investigations that are enhanced and supported by free and open access to biodiversity data from the GBIF network of Participants, nodes and publishers."
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:206
#, no-wrap
msgid "intro-to-gbif::GBIF-for-Science-Slide5.png"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:209
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Slide 5 - Systematic reviews of GBIF-enabled science*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:211
msgid "As more and more researchers cite data using DOIs, GBIF is better able to monitor and to analyze the landscape of GBIF-enabled science. Every five years the corpus of GBIF enabled research is a subject of systematic review, exploring the patterns of GBIF use in research."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:213
msgid "On the left, you can see diversity of topics in years 2016 to 2019, the topics becoming hotter and cooler with time, topic connections, and topic sizes, and the picture on the right outlines the thematic relevance landscape of GBIF in more recently from 2020 to 2024."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:215
msgid "These studies produce two kinds of important fact-based signals for the network: they outline the evolution of the GBIF data outputs for scientific analyses, and the strategic understanding of GBIF position and trends in supporting science."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block _
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:222
msgid "https://doi.org/10.1073/pnas.2018093118 Heberling et al. 2021 Data integration enables global biodiversity synthesis 2016 – 2019 DOI: 10.1073/pnas.2018093118"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block _
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:227
msgid "https://doi.org/10.1073/pnas.2519119122 Steinke et al. 2025 Globally aggregated biodiversity data impact predictive and descriptive research 2020 – 2024"
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:229
#, no-wrap
msgid "intro-to-gbif::GBIF-for-Science-Slide6.png"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:232
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Slide 6 - GBIF-enabled science: research topics over time: 2010 – 2024*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:234
msgid "What kind of signals and patterns do these systematic reviews reveal? GBIF-powered studies were mostly focuse on ecology in combination with conservation, climate change, agriculture, phylogenetics, evolution, taxonomy, and species distribution. The prevalence of the topics have changed over time — especially ecology in combination with climate change (since 2019), and agriculture (a jump in 2023)."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block _
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:237
msgid "Steinke D et al. (2025): Globally aggregated biodiversity data impacts predictive and descriptive research. PNAS 122(50): e2519119122. https://doi.org/10.1073/pnas.2519119122"
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:239
#, no-wrap
msgid "intro-to-gbif::GBIF-for-Science-Slide7.png"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:242
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Slide 7 - GBIF thematic relevance*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:244
msgid "Data shared through GBIF is https://www.gbif.org/composition/2SEGqoMS8eMVos9T1owEEk[applied across many disciplines and research traditions^]. To name just a few:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:246
msgid "CONSERVATION, including conservation biology but also science-based management, such as design of the protect areas and assessment of threats to species, by tracking the actual and predicted spread of invasive alien species."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:248
msgid "In relation to Agrobiodiversity, GBIF mediated data help exploring distribution of the crop wild relatives."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:250
msgid "Another human related sector is HUMAN HEALTH where species that act as vectors, hosts and reservoirs of human diseases are discoverable through GBIF."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:252
msgid "As GBIF provides access to both historic and to recent biodiversity data, GBIF powers research on effect of the environmental CHANGE onto species and communities, often using modelling techniques where GBIF mediated data serve as baseline and as inputs."
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:253
#, no-wrap
msgid "intro-to-gbif::GBIF-for-Science-Slide8.png"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:256
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Slide 8 - Mision and Vision*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:258
msgid "GBIF exists to build the evidence to advance scientific research and to support global understanding of biodiversity. GBIF relevance for science and research is the most visible and the best documented thanks for DOI based literature tracking. GBIF coordinates international scientific efforts of GBIF on its mission of making biodiversity data openly available to all countries and individuals."
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:259
#, no-wrap
msgid "intro-to-gbif::GBIF-for-Science-Slide9.png"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:262
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Slide 9 - Conclusion*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:264
msgid "This video is part of a series of presentations developed for the Introduction to GBIF course. It was created and narrated by me, Dmitry Schigel. If you have any questions on the course content, you can reach out at training@gbif.org."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/about-gbif.adoc:268
#, no-wrap
msgid "GBIF Participant Nodes"
msgstr ""

